                  <p>
                    Caroline's warm, engaging personality creates a natural, positive, and fun therapeutic environment. Her passion for working with young children and their families is palpable; she is happiest and most fulfilled when helping children reach their goals. Caroline also emphasizes the importance of communication. She believes that regular contact between therapists, parents, teachers, and specialists facilitates the most growth and ensures carryover of skills across all environments.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    Caroline's previous experience with the pediatric population includes work in a therapeutic preschool setting, public school setting, and private practice. She has experience evaluating and treating children with a variety of communication disorders, including autism spectrum disorders, receptive/ expressive language delays, articulation/ phonology disorders, social-pragmatic language disorders, and feeding disorders.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    Caroline earned her Bachelor of Arts in Communication Disorders from Loyola University Maryland and her Master of Science in Speech-Language Pathology from Towson University in Baltimore, Maryland.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    Caroline currently resides in Boston, and enjoys running, reading, cooking, and spending time with her family.
                  </p>

